Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, remove the @Slow Cooked British Chicken{290%g} from its packaging and place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices. Cover with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the chicken is piping hot throughout.

In the meantime, trim the @Green Beans{150%g}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled) or use a #garlic press{}.

When the chicken has 10 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn the heat down to medium, add a splash of @water{}, and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once tender, add half the @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and garlic to the pan. Cook for ~{1%minute} more, then remove from the heat.

Once cooked, remove the chicken from the oven, discard the foil, then use two #forks{} to gently break apart the chicken.

Stir through the @Gochujang Paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Honey{15%g} and remaining soy until combined.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the gochujang chicken and soy green beans.

Drizzle over the @Mayonnaise{32%g} and finish with a sprinkle of @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!